# Deploy Test — CivicQ Landing Page (live verification)

Ran a real Playwright (chromium) session against the live deployment
(michaelwegter.com + api.michaelwegter.com), plus direct `fetch` calls to the
API. Script: `upwork-runs/civicq/deploy-test.spec.js`. Playwright 1.61.0,
chromium downloaded fresh for this check.

## Routes / pages

| Check | Result |
|---|---|
| `GET https://michaelwegter.com/work-samples/civicq` | Resolves via GH Pages SPA fallback (initial network request is 404, `404.html` JS-redirects to the React route, final loaded page title = "CivicQ Landing Page — Michael Wegter") |
| `<iframe>` on that page points at | `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/civicq/` ✓ |
| `GET https://michaelwegter.com/demos/civicq/` | **200** |
| `GET https://michaelwegter.com/demos/civicq/methodology.html` | **200** |

**Note on the 404 console line:** the first network request to
`/work-samples/civicq` does log `Failed to load resource: 404`. This is not a
civicq-specific bug — it's the universal GH Pages SPA mechanism every
work-sample on this site uses (`public/404.html` catches the unknown path,
stores it, then JS-redirects). Verified by loading an existing, already-live
route (`/work-samples/repsetta-fitness`) with the same script: it produces the
identical single 404 console line and still resolves correctly. Both pages
end up fully rendered with correct titles, so this is expected, pre-existing
site behavior, not a regression introduced by this demo.

## Hero flow / page content (on `/demos/civicq/`)

| Check | Result |
|---|---|
| Hero / CivicQ branding visible | ✓ |
| Sticky nav links present | ✓ (15 nav/header links) |
| Anchor-link sections found | ✓ `#main #top #why-it-matters #features #scoring #status #org-hub #funding #partners ...` — all 10 spec sections reachable via anchor nav |
| Custom data viz rendered (SVG) | ✓ 10 `<svg>` elements on the landing page (scoring chart + funds breakdown + org-hub wireframe + decorative) |
| Methodology page link present | ✓ (3 links to methodology.html) |
| Methodology page renders | ✓ 200, 3 SVGs present |

## Email capture -> live backend (multi-step workflow)

1. Filled the email input on the live demo page with a unique test address.
2. Clicked the subscribe/submit control.
3. Page fired a real network request to `https://api.michaelwegter.com/api/civicq/subscribe`.
4. API responded **201 Created**, `{"message":"Subscribed.","status":"success"}`.

Confirms the end-to-end flow (browser form -> live API -> SQLite) works on
the actual production deployment, not just locally.

## Direct API checks

| Endpoint | Result |
|---|---|
| `GET https://api.michaelwegter.com/health` | **200** `{"status":"ok","version":"1.0.0"}` |
| `POST https://api.michaelwegter.com/api/civicq/subscribe` | **201**, success body |
| `GET https://api.michaelwegter.com/api/civicq/csv-export` | **200**, CSV body with header `email,created_at` and prior test rows (including the row written by the in-browser submission above, confirming the browser flow and the direct API hit the same persisted store) |

## Console errors during all page loads

Only the single, pre-existing, site-wide GH Pages 404-redirect line discussed
above (also reproduced on an unrelated, already-shipped work-sample route).
No JS exceptions, no failed asset loads, no React errors, no CORS errors, no
broken API calls.

## Problems found

None that are specific to this demo or block the gate. The one console line
investigated is confirmed to be an existing site-wide mechanism, not a defect
introduced by this run.

VERDICT: pass
